Fixes #85918

## Summary

- Recover complete DeepSeek DSML invoke blocks on the OpenAI-compatible completions stream when tools were actually exposed and the invoke name matches a declared tool.
- Preserve the existing DSML visible-text stripping behavior, prefer native `tool_calls` when present, and cap retained DSML bodies.
- Add regression coverage for parameter semantics, split chunks, native-shadow de-dupe, trailing text ordering, disabled/unknown tools, malformed DSML, tool-choice narrowing, structured thinking, and oversized DSML bodies.

## Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: DeepSeek/Foundry completions streams that emit complete DSML tool-call markup as assistant text now become executable tool calls instead of visible/filtered text, while native `tool_calls` remain authoritative.

Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on this PR branch, rebased onto current `upstream/main`, executed through `createOpenAICompletionsTransportStreamFn` against a local HTTP/SSE server that emulates an OpenAI-compatible `/v1/chat/completions` streaming endpoint with DeepSeek compatibility enabled.

Exact steps or command run after this patch: `node --import tsx --input-type=module` with a local OpenClaw transport smoke that starts a loopback HTTP server, calls `createOpenAICompletionsTransportStreamFn`, sends a request containing declared tool `session_status`, returns an SSE chunk containing `<|DSML|tool_calls>`, and records the emitted OpenClaw stream events.

Evidence after fix: Terminal output from the local OpenClaw transport smoke:

```json
{
  "httpRequest": {
    "path": "/v1/chat/completions",
    "stream": true,
    "toolNames": [
      "session_status"
    ],
    "model": "deepseek-v4-pro",
    "toolChoice": "auto"
  },
  "streamEvents": [
    {
      "type": "start"
    },
    {
      "type": "text_start",
      "contentIndex": 0
    },
    {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "delta": "before ",
      "contentIndex": 0
    },
    {
      "type": "toolcall_start",
      "contentIndex": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "toolcall_delta",
      "delta": "{\"sessionKey\":\"current\"}",
      "contentIndex": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "text_start",
      "contentIndex": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "delta": " after",
      "contentIndex": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "done",
      "reason": "toolUse"
    }
  ],
  "final": {
    "doneReason": "toolUse",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "before "
      },
      {
        "type": "toolCall",
        "id": "call_deepseek_dsml_0",
        "name": "session_status",
        "arguments": {
          "sessionKey": "current"
        },
        "partialArgs": "{\"sessionKey\":\"current\"}"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " after"
      }
    ],
    "leakedDsml": false
  }
}
```

Observed result after fix: The transport sent the declared `session_status` tool to the OpenAI-compatible endpoint, DSML text did not leak into emitted stream events, the declared invocation was recovered as a `toolCall`, surrounding visible text stayed ordered around the recovered call, and the final stop reason changed to `toolUse`.

What was not tested: Live Microsoft Foundry/DeepSeek provider call; no provider credentials used.

